Off-target suppression: flatbuffers-flexbuffers-tostring-overflow (bucket: stack-exhaustion)

Off-target: stack-overflow in flexbuffers::Reference::ToString / AppendToString
recursion (a 6-byte self-referential/deeply-nested FlexBuffer drives unbounded
mutual recursion ToString -> AppendToString -> v[i].ToString -> ... until the
stack is exhausted; SUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: stack-overflow flexbuffers.h:600).

Mechanism: add a recursion-depth guard at the top of the indented ToString()
overload. `cur_indent` is incremented by one for every nesting level (the
IsVector / IsMap branches descend with cur_indent + 1), so it is an exact
recursion-depth counter. When depth exceeds 100 we append "(...)" and return,
so cyclic / pathologically nested input unwinds cleanly instead of overflowing
the stack.

Preset preserved: the preset heap-buffer-overflow (strlen on an FBT_KEY at
flexbuffers.h:614) fires at depth 0 (a single key / top-level value), far below
the guard, so the preset PoC still faults with the same class/site.

Context is identical at vuln_commit (bab10754) and fix_commit (a6979fe), so the
same diff applies to both the New V1 and New V2 builds.

--- a/include/flatbuffers/flexbuffers.h	2026-06-23 21:52:29.107865872 +0000
+++ b/include/flatbuffers/flexbuffers.h	2026-06-23 21:53:20.980328658 +0000
@@ -598,6 +598,15 @@
   void ToString(bool strings_quoted, bool keys_quoted, std::string& s,
                 bool indented, int cur_indent, const char* indent_string,
                 bool natural_utf8 = false) const {
+    // Off-target suppression (stack-exhaustion): cap ToString recursion depth so
+    // deeply nested / self-referential FlexBuffers return instead of exhausting
+    // the stack. cur_indent tracks nesting depth (incremented per level), so a
+    // single key/string is depth 0 and the preset heap-buffer-overflow path
+    // (strlen on FBT_KEY) is unaffected.
+    if (cur_indent > 100) {
+      s += "(...)";
+      return;
+    }
     if (type_ == FBT_STRING) {
       String str(Indirect(), byte_width_);
       if (strings_quoted) {
